    <h2>WARRANTY COMPARISON</h2>

    <p>Both manufacturers offer tiered warranty programs, and understanding the differences is important because the warranty is only as strong as its terms.</p>

    <h3>GAF Warranty Tiers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Standard Warranty</strong> — Lifetime limited on materials; available to all customers regardless of installer</li>
      <li><strong>System Plus</strong> — Adds workmanship coverage when GAF accessories (starter strip, ridge cap, underlayment) are used with the shingles. Available through any installer.</li>
      <li><strong>Silver Pledge</strong> — 10-year workmanship coverage backed by GAF (not the installer). Requires a GAF Certified Installer and full GAF accessory system.</li>
      <li><strong>Golden Pledge</strong> — 25-year workmanship coverage backed by GAF. The gold standard. Requires a GAF Master Elite installer and full GAF system.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Owens Corning Warranty Tiers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Standard Warranty</strong> — Lifetime limited on materials; available to all customers</li>
      <li><strong>Preferred Protection</strong> — Adds 10-year workmanship coverage. Requires an OC Preferred Contractor and OC components.</li>
      <li><strong>Platinum Protection</strong> — Adds 25-year workmanship coverage. Requires a Platinum-level OC contractor and full OC system.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The key takeaway: to get the best warranty from either manufacturer, you need a certified installer using that manufacturer's full system of products (shingles + starter strip + ridge cap + underlayment). Happy Roof can provide enhanced warranties from both manufacturers.</p>

    <h2>PRICING</h2>

    <p>In Tampa Bay, GAF and Owens Corning shingles are priced within a few dollars per bundle of each other for comparable product lines. The Timberline HDZ and Duration are typically within 5-10% of each other in installed cost. Premium lines (UHDZ, Camelot, Berkshire) carry a noticeable premium over the standard architectural offerings.</p>

    <p>The installed cost of a shingle roof is driven far more by labor, decking condition, roof complexity, and accessory materials than by the per-bundle shingle price difference between GAF and Owens Corning. In other words, choosing one brand over the other is unlikely to significantly change your total project cost.</p>

    <h2>OUR RECOMMENDATION</h2>

    <p>Both brands are excellent, and we are confident recommending either one to Tampa Bay homeowners. That said, here are some general guidelines:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Choose GAF if</strong> color selection is a priority, you want the most widely available product for easy future matching, or you prefer the longest algae protection warranty (StainGuard Plus)</li>
      <li><strong>Choose Owens Corning if</strong> you value SureNail's fastener technology and visible nail line, you are interested in the Duration FLEX for impact resistance, or you prefer the TruDefinition color depth</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The most important factor in your roof's performance is not which shingle brand you choose — it is the quality of the installation. A perfectly installed Owens Corning roof and a perfectly installed GAF roof will both protect your home for decades. A poorly installed roof with either brand will fail. <a href="/blog/5-questions-to-ask-your-roofer">Choose your contractor</a> at least as carefully as you choose your shingle brand.</p>

